        "collapsible_tab_Ta8cMT": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Made in Italy",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>Our <strong>Breton Shirts</strong> are crafted just a few kilometers from <strong>Venice</strong>, in a region known for its rich artisanal heritage and its role in producing garments for the world’s top <strong>high-fashion brands</strong>.</p><p>Each piece is meticulously made from <strong>fine merino wool</strong>, prized for its natural <strong>softness</strong> and <strong>thermo-regulating properties</strong>, ensuring comfort in any season.</p><p>We collaborate with a <strong>small, family-run workshop</strong>, fostering a partnership built on <strong>trust, craftsmanship, and a passion for quality</strong>—values that define every garment we create.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_9wCejz": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "100% Recycled Cotton",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>We have selected a 100% recycled cotton gabardine weighing 650 grams — a fabric chosen for its substance and depth rather than economy.<br/><br/>Sourced from a long-established supplier in the province of Treviso, active in the textile industry for over fifty years, it reflects consistent quality built through experience rather than trend.<br/><br/>The dense gabardine weave gives the jacket structure and definition, holding its silhouette while remaining comfortable to wear. Its weight adds presence and durability, while the recycled cotton offers a balanced, refined hand feel.<br/><br/>Selected for its character and longevity, it represents a considered approach to material — one that values quality and responsible sourcing without compromise.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_T6nwD3": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Handmade Embroidery",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>Our Marinières are hand embroidered with needle and thread, making each one unique. </p><p>Each pieces is also hand numbered, from 1 to 99.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "47bfb772-5b4f-4198-802a-23f7ca18048d": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Fit",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>This Jacket is designed for a regular fit.<br/><br/>Available from S to L. We recommend ordering your normal size. If you are unsure or need some advice, send us a message and we will be happy to help.<br/><br/>The model in the photo is 173 cm tall and wears size M.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "e9567a30-a8a4-47b3-ac6b-dd845b2d3a7c": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Yarn & Care",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>We craft our French Work Jacket in Italy using 100% recycled cotton gabardine, selected for its density and structure rather than mass-produced fabric. Every jacket is cut and sewn by skilled artisans, preserving the authenticity of classic workwear while refining it through contemporary proportions.<br/><br/>The jacket <strong>can be machine washed at 30°C</strong> and hung to dry. As with all garment-dyed pieces, wear is part of the process. Over time, the fabric softens, adapting naturally to the movements of its owner. Subtle variations in tone, gentle creases and lived-in nuances will gradually appear, shaped by daily use and the body itself.<br/><br/>These <strong>variations are not imperfections</strong>, but the defining characteristic of raw denim — a material designed to evolve and become uniquely personal with time.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "d808420e-8e92-4566-9948-7577a69f3f77": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Shipping & Returns",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p><strong>Shipping is free worldwide.</strong></p><p>Once your Marinière or Jacket is dispatched, you'll receive an email with tracking details. We ship all over the world. And if you’re based in the EU, we will be sending your items directly from Italy so that you won’t incur additional customs fees.</p><p>If for any reason you wanted to return your Marinière, we accept returns within 14 days of delivery as long as the Marinièere or Jacket is in perfect condition.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
