    "rich_text_Fn6rqL": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_f7pQBT": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "A Certain Way to Wear It",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "text_nExUGk": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>There’s a certain way to wear it. Not rigid. Not nostalgic. Slightly undone, but deliberate.<br/>Edition 07 feels at ease between the Mediterranean coast and Paris — less holiday, more attitude. Morning light cutting across wide boulevards. A French Work Jacket resting on the shoulders on the way to a Sunday market, espresso in hand, newspapers folded under the arm. Underneath, Breton stripes — the quiet kind — breaking the silhouette with a familiar rhythm.<br/>Later, an opening in a gallery-lined district. Conversations held close. Cuffs folded back without ceremony. A long table in a discreet bistrot where the room is understated and the people are not.<br/>And sometimes, a Vespa leaving the city just before sunset — the jacket catching the wind, the Breton effortless against the movement.<br/>It moves easily through the creative quarters, onto warm pavement, into salt air, or out beyond the périphérique where the road opens and the light changes.<br/>It’s the kind of collection that works in motion as much as at rest.<br/>Effortless, but intentional. Relaxed, but precise.<br/>Parisian in spirit. Distressed only where it matters.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
